---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Baseline Financial Freedom | Makeaway"
  description="A short money article about building a basic level of financial freedom through control, savings, debt reduction, and practical habits."
>
  <main class="article-page">
    <a class="back-link" href="/money/">← Back to Money</a>

    <article class="article">
      <p class="eyebrow">Makeaway / Money</p>

      <h1>Baseline Financial Freedom</h1>

      <p class="intro">
        Financial freedom does not have to start with being rich. It starts with
        getting control.
      </p>

      <p>
        A lot of people think financial freedom means never working again. That
        may be the long-term dream, but the first level is much simpler: having
        enough control over your money that every problem does not become a
        crisis.
      </p>

      <p>
        Baseline financial freedom means building space between you and panic.
        It means having some savings, lowering bad debt, understanding where your
        money goes, and creating options for yourself.
      </p>

      <p>
        The goal is not to look rich. The goal is to become harder to trap.
      </p>

      <p>
        That can start small. Cook at home more. Cancel things you do not use.
        Pay down one balance. Build an emergency fund. Learn a skill that can
        make money. Invest slowly and consistently. Stop letting convenience
        drain your future.
      </p>

      <p>
        Money is not the whole path, but it is part of the path. The more control
        you have over your money, the more room you have to make better choices.
      </p>

      <p>
        Baseline financial freedom is not about luxury. It is about stability.
        It is about breathing room. It is about creating enough margin to stop
        living completely at the mercy of the next bill, the next emergency, or
        the next bad job.
      </p>

      <p>
        Start there. Build the base. Then keep going.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article-page {
    width: min(900px, calc(100% - 2rem));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 800;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--text-main);
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-main);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 5rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.06em;
  }

  .intro {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-main);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .article p {
    max-width: 760px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .article p + p {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .article-page {
      padding: 2.5rem 0;
    }
  }
</style>